{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-tag-page-js","path":"/tag/twitter","result":{"pageContext":{"tag":"twitter","tags":["python","beginners",null,"kedro","blog","webdev","data","git","bash","actions","catalytic","vim","linux","cli","twitter"],"tagCounts":{"python":82,"beginners":50,"null":19,"blog":9,"webdev":8,"cli":1,"catalytic":4,"twitter":1,"data":8,"linux":3,"bash":6,"actions":6,"git":8,"kedro":10,"vim":4},"posts":[{"node":{"id":"661a801e-02a0-59e0-902e-7818e38a76f2","html":"<p>Can someone explain how or why twitter cards render differently from device to device?  I do understand that twitter cards a built from meta tags, the full list can be found in their <a href=\"https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/tweets/optimize-with-cards/overview/markup\">docs</a></p>\n<h2>Rendered on Mobile</h2>\n<p>Mobile Looks fine.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://waylonwalker.com/twitter-card-rendered.png\" alt=\"rendered card\"></p>\n<h2>Not Rendered on Desktop</h2>\n<p>On Desktop it is not picking up the image.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://waylonwalker.com/twitter-card-rendered.png\" alt=\"not rendered card\"></p>\n<h2>Twitter Card Validator</h2>\n<p>The Validator renders the card correctly.  I tried the official <a href=\"https://cards-dev.twitter.com/validator\">twitter card validator</a>, as well as <a href=\"https://www.heymeta.com/url/waylonwalker.com/latest\">heymeta.com</a>, and <a href=\"https://metatags.io/\">metatags.io</a>.  All look good.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://waylonwalker.com/twitter-card-rendered.png\" alt=\"rendered card with validator\"></p>\n<h2>Can Cards be updated?</h2>\n<p><em>even with a redirect?</em></p>\n<p>I tried seting up a pinned tweet that uses a netlify redirect to always keep my latest post up to date.  Again this one looks good in the validator, doesnt render the image on desktop, does render the image on mobile, but does not update.  I have heard that you need to hit the card validator to update cards?  I am not sure if this is true, but for me this is not even upating the card.</p>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">👋 Hello,<br><br>―――――― I&#39;m Waylon Walker ――――――<br><br>I work with data using 🐍 <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/python?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#python</a> and utilize <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/webdev?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#webdev</a> to 〽visualize it.<br><br>――――――<br><br>I write about things on my 🌱 digital garden<a href=\"https://t.co/rAvD9iw05g\">https://t.co/rAvD9iw05g</a><br><br>👨‍💻Some are cross-posted to <a href=\"https://t.co/oRWk7MgUD5\">https://t.co/oRWk7MgUD5</a><br><br>――――――<br>💌<a href=\"https://t.co/PilOTWQ9ub\">https://t.co/PilOTWQ9ub</a></p>&mdash; 𝚆𝚊𝚢𝚕𝚘𝚗 𝚆𝚊𝚕𝚔𝚎𝚛 (@_WaylonWalker) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/_WaylonWalker/status/1282000623299371008?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">July 11, 2020</a></blockquote> <script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>","fields":{"slug":"/explain-twitter-cards/"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["blog","twitter"],"title":"🙋‍♂️ Can Anyone Explain Twitter Cards to me?","description":"Can someone explain how or why twitter cards render differently from device to device? I do understand that twitter cards a built from meta tags, the full list can be found in their","templateKey":"blog-post","status":"published","date":"2020-07-11T03:00:00.000Z","cover":{"med_img":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":500,"height":210,"src":"/static/21b1e03ac6d2afebe99e9ed2672d8127/46604/explain-twitter-cards-xmas2020.png","srcSet":"/static/21b1e03ac6d2afebe99e9ed2672d8127/46604/explain-twitter-cards-xmas2020.png 1x,\n/static/21b1e03ac6d2afebe99e9ed2672d8127/d8815/explain-twitter-cards-xmas2020.png 1.5x,\n/static/21b1e03ac6d2afebe99e9ed2672d8127/31987/explain-twitter-cards-xmas2020.png 2x"}},"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":200,"height":85,"src":"/static/21b1e03ac6d2afebe99e9ed2672d8127/71e30/explain-twitter-cards-xmas2020.png","srcSet":"/static/21b1e03ac6d2afebe99e9ed2672d8127/71e30/explain-twitter-cards-xmas2020.png 1x,\n/static/21b1e03ac6d2afebe99e9ed2672d8127/24123/explain-twitter-cards-xmas2020.png 1.5x,\n/static/21b1e03ac6d2afebe99e9ed2672d8127/492a0/explain-twitter-cards-xmas2020.png 2x"}}}}}}]}},"staticQueryHashes":["2992646504"]}